---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Kiefer Taylor Land" description="Learn about Kiefer Taylor Land — from military family roots in Japan to music, cybersecurity, and software testing.">
  <Header />
  <main>
    <h1>About Me</h1>

    <p>
      I'm Kiefer Taylor Land — a software tester, cybersecurity professional, and lifelong 
      tech enthusiast based in the Pacific Northwest (currently Redmond, WA, heading back to 
      San Diego soon).
    </p>

    <h2>Early Life</h2>
    <p>
      Born at Yokosuka Naval Hospital in Japan in 1989 to prior military parents, I grew up 
      moving around a lot. The most formative years were ages 9–13 when we lived in Japan 
      again — those core memories and my love for Japanese culture have stayed with me ever 
      since. Japan holds a special place in my heart.
    </p>

    <h2>Music</h2>
    <p>
      I picked up guitar at 13 and never put it down. Played in various bands throughout high 
      school and beyond. That love for music sparked an interest in production and audio 
      engineering — I started DJing and producing on my laptop, and eventually attended the 
      LA Recording School in Hollywood, graduating with an AS in Recording Arts in December 2012.
    </p>

    <h2>Tech Career</h2>
    <p>
      I've always been drawn to technology. My earliest memories are playing the original Game 
      Boy and Super Nintendo, followed by Sega Genesis, N64, and PlayStation 1 & 2.
    </p>
    <p>
      My professional tech journey started in 2021 when I moved to San Diego and began on an 
      IT help desk. From there I worked my way up to sysadmin, went back to school for a 
      Bachelor's and Master's in Cybersecurity & Information Assurance, and transitioned into 
      software testing in 2023 — which is where I am today.
    </p>

    <h2>What I'm Building Toward</h2>
    <p>
      My goal is to sell services for testing AI/LLM behavior and security, leveraging my 
      cybersecurity background and software testing experience. Long term, I want to build 
      products in this space. The intersection of AI security and quality assurance is where 
      I believe I can make a real impact.
    </p>

    <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">
      <a href="/">← Back to Home</a> · <a href="/blog/">Read the Blog</a>
    </p>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
